COMMANDS

&3Usage:&n &4commands&n

The COMMANDS command gives a canonical list of all the known verbs.

Each command listed should have help available by typing "HELP <command>".

See also: SOCIAL, SOCIALS
#
COMPACT

&2Compact&n

&3Usage:&n &4compact&n

This command toggles the extra blank line output to your screen after each
command.  Useful if you have a small display.

See also: BRIEF
#
CONSIDER

&3Usage:&n &4consider <mob>&n

This command will compare your Level with the <mobs> level.  You will then
receive a rough estimate, which is by no means exact.  Consider does not take
hitpoints/special attacks/damage into account.

See also: HIT, KILL
#
DIAGNOSE

&2Diagnose&n
&3Usage:&n &4diagnose <mob>&n

The DIAGNOSE command tells you how wounded a character looks.  If you are
fighting someone, you can use DIAGNOSE with no arguments to diagnose the
person you're fighting.

See also: CONSIDER
#
DIE

&2Die&n

&3Usage:&n &4order clones die&n
This feature is for when you no longer require your clones.
With this your clones will die.

See also:  CLONES SERVE ORDER
#
DISPLAY PROMPT

&2Display Prompt&n

&3Usage:&n &4display < H | M | V | | X | L | all | on | off | set prompt_string>&n

Modify your prompt to show your hit/mana/movement points, alignment or
experience to next level.

Example:
  > &4display hv&n                  Display hit points and movement points
  > &4display off&n                 Return to normal display
  > &4display all&n                 Display hit, mana, and move points

User definable prompts are a new feature as &RPrimalMUD&n version 3. The following
identifiers are translated:
&4%h&n      Current hit points      &4%H&n      Max hit points
&4%m&n      Current mana points     &4%M&n      Max mana points
&4%v&n      Current move points     &4%V&n      Max move points
&4%l&n      Alignment
&4%x&n      Experience to next level

User definable prompts are set given the &4set&n argument followed by the
string. Prompt strings longer than &c25&n chars are truncated. Easy colour
codes can be used within the string.

Example:
Current primal complete prompt - equivilant to &4prompt all&n
  > &4display set %hH %mM %vV X:%x &&RAl:%x&n      
&G250&nH &r35&nM &Y107&nV X:&G1.9m &RAl:&n123 >

Custom hit points prompt displaying current of maximum hit points
  > &4display set &&RMyPrompt&&n: %h/%H&n          
&RMyPrompt&n: &Y231&n/&G250&n >

See also: TOGGLE
#
"DISMOUNT"

&2Usage:&n  &4dismount&n

If you find yourself mounted on a mob that is capable of being ridden this is the
command you use to get off the poor thing!

See also: Breakin & Mount
#
DONATE

&2Donate&n

&3Usage:&n &4donate <object>
       donate <number> coin&n

This command takes an object that you no longer want and deposits it in the
donation room of Haven to assist newbies in getting started.  

Examples:
  > &4donate shield&n
  > &4donate all.bread&n
  > &4donate 500 coins&n

See also: &3JUNK&n
