If you're hungry or thirsty, these commands are for you!

Example:
  > eat bread
  > taste bread
  > drink cup
  > sip fountain
#
EMOTE :

&2Emote :&n

&3Usage:&n &4emote <message>
       : <message>&n

Show people what you're feeling.  The shorthand is ":".
Your name will be displayed followed by the string.

Example:

If your name is "Helt",

  > emote is feeling very sad today.

will display:

Helt is feeling very sad today.

See also: SOCIALS
#
ENTER

&2Enter&n

&3Usage:&n &4enter
       enter <place>&n
       
If you type 'enter' while you are outdoors, you'll enter any nearby shelter.
You can also follow 'enter' with an argument. 

Example :
  
  > enter window
#
EQUIPMENT

&2Equipment&n

&3Usage:&n &4equipment&n
           &4equipment <where>&n
	   &4equipment empty&n

Gives you a list of all the equipment you're wearing, holding, and wielding.

If <where> is specified, gives you a list of the equipment you're wearing in
the specified position.

If empty is specified, gives you a list of positions you have yet to wear
something on.

Example :

  > equipment finger
  > equipment light

See also: INVENTORY, REMOVE, WEAR
#
EXAMINE

&2Examine&n

&3Usage:&n &4examine <thing to examine>&n

May give you some valuable information about an item or mob.
Examine will show the inventory of a mob or object unlike look
which will not.

See also: LOOK
#
EXITS

&2Exits&n
&3Usage:&n &4exits&n

Gives you a list of the obvious exits from your location.  Of course, the less
obvious ones won't show up here - you have to THINK in order to locate those.

See also: AUTOEXIT
#
FILL

&2Fill&n

&3Usage:&n &4fill <item> <object to fill from>&n

If you want to fill a container you're holding with liquid from a fountain
in the same room as you.

Example:

  > fill canteen fountain

See also: POUR
#
FLEE

&2Flee&n

&3Usage:&n &4flee&n

If you are in a fight and things are beginning to get a little uncomfortable
(maybe you are dying), just type 'flee', and presto!  You are out of harms way
- that is, IF there is a suitable exit nearby, and IF that exit doesn't simply
bring you from the ashes to the fire and IF you can get away from the creature 
you are fighting... but then, who wants to live forever?

See also: WIMPY
#
FOLLOW

&2Follow&n

&3Usage:&n &4follow <leader | player | self | mob>&n

Use FOLLOW to automatically follow someone else.

Examples:

  > follow splat
  > follow self

See also: GROUP, SNEAK
#
FRIEND

&2friend&n

&3Usage:&n &4friend <playername>&n

This command will allow you to assign friends to your character.
These players you list as friends are able to pick up your corpse
and return it to you when you re-connect. So becarefull who you 
choose as a friend as this will enable them to raid your corpse!

See Also: Autocorpse
#
GET TAKE

&2Get Take

&3Usage:&n &4get <object>
       get <object>
       get <object> all.<object>
       get all <object>
       get all.<object>
       get all.<object> all.<object>&n
       
"Get" and "take" are exactly the same and can be used interchangeably.
If you find something interesting on the ground, you may use 'get' to pick
it up.  'get' can also be used to extract items from containers.

Examples:
  > get sword
  > get sword all.corpse
  > get all corpse
  > get all all.bag
  > get all.bread all.bag

See also: DROP, PUT
#
GIVE

&2Give&n

&3Usage:&n &4give all <victim>
       give <object> <victim>
       give all.<object> <victim>
       give <number> coins <victim>&n

If you feel benevolent, you may give some stuff to someone in need.

  > give all &7sandii&n
  > give bread &6citizen&n
  > give all.bronze &7mirlen&n
  > give &Y40000&n coins &7splat&n

See also: &3GET, DROP, JUNK, DONATE, PUT, WEAR, GRAB, REMOVE, EXAMINE&n
#
