#
"ITEMHUNT QUEST" "ITEM HUNT QUEST"

&2Itemhunt Quests&n

&3Itemhunt Specific Quest Commands:&n
&4  quest locate&n  - Will locate any unclaimed items, at a cost of 10 mana.
&4  quest restore&n - Will restore your health, mana and movement in exchange
                      for a small amount of experience.
An itemhunt quest takes place in a zone designated by an imm, who will also
determine the item being searched. These are both viewable using the
&4quest info&n command (See the help on "quest"). Random mobiles, not
not necessarily from that zone, or even world, will be loaded at random
locations. These mobiles will each have between zero and two of the quest
items.

When you retrieve the item from the corpse, your score will be automatically
incremented, and broadcast to the quest participants.

When a new mobile is loaded, it will be broadcast to the participants.

Hint: You might try using "where <mob>" to get a better idea of where to find
your target.

See Also: QUEST, "TRIVIA QUEST"
#
"TRIVIA QUEST"

&2Trivia Quests&n

&3Trivia Specific Quest Commands:&n
&4  quest question&n - Displays the current question.
&4  quest answer x &n- Submit your answer of 'x'.

A trivia quest will consist of an imm firing trivia questions through the
quest system. The first person two answer the question correctly will score
a point. This will repeat until either the questions are exhausted, or a
player reaches a certain score.

See Also: QUEST, "ITEMHUNT QUEST"
#
