QUAFF POTION POTIONS

&2Quaff Potion Potions&n

&3Usage:&n &4quaff <potion>&n

Potions are available at the Alchemists store in Haven, and elsewhere
around the world.  Potions will do varied things, from Cure Light
through to Poison.  Potions can be Quaffed, as shown below.

The magic will take effect immediately, for better or for worse...

Example: 
  > quaff red

#
"QUEST"

&2Quest&n

&3Usage:&n &4quest&n       - Show available commands.
       &4quest join&n  - Join the current quest.
       &4quest leave&n - Leave the current quest.
       &4quest info&n  - View details on the current quest.
       &4quest score&n - See the current quest scoreboard.

The quest command is the core command to most things quest related. With the
exceptions of qsay and questlog. For more information see the help on 
"trivia quest" and "itemhunt quest".

More quest types may be added in the future.

See also: QSAY QUESTLOG "ITEMHUNT QUEST" "TRIVIA QUEST"
#
"QUESTLOG"

&2Questlog&n

&3Usage:&n  &4questlog&n

This will tell you what quest items you have listed in your name. To get
a quest item logged against your name you have to win quests! The log is
designed to control the quest equipment and this means that once an item
is logged against your name you can not share it with another player and
everytime you log onto the game the item will automatically load for you.
You will no longer lose your quest equipment through dying.

See Also: Quest QSay
#
QUIT QUI 

&2Quit&n

Quit will make the game save your character and your equipment then you
will exit the game.  When quiting the equipment will save to the position
you are wearing them. This means when you come back to the game you are 
already wearing your 'eq'.

See also: HOUSES
#
