BUG TYPO IDEA TODO

&2Bug Typo Idea Todo&n

&3Usage: &4[bug | idea | typo | todo] <option>&n

&3    options:&n 
&3    	add 
	edit <number> 
	delete <number>
	list ['self' | <state> | <player>]
	print <number>

&3add&n: 	creates a new report
&3edit&n:	edits the given report
&3delete&n:	deletes the given report
&3list&n:	lists existing reports, 
		optionally filtered by ['self' | <state> | <&7player&n>]
  'self': 	lists only the reports that you are responsible for.
  <state>:	lists reports only of the given state 
  		(OPEN, ASSESSED, FEEDBACK, CLOSED)
  <player>:	lists only the reports that <player> is responsible for
&3print&n:	displays the full details of the given report	

For full information about &RPrimalMUD's&n reporting system type &4help reporting&n.

See also: &3REPORTING, LISTREPORTS, PRINTREPORT&n
#
"REPORTING SYSTEM"

&2Reporting System&n

&RPrimalMUD&n version 3 saw the implementation of a new reporting system.
This report management system allows players to use a menu based system to 
add information about the &4bug&n/&4typo&n/&4idea&n/&4todo&n report. It is designed to provide
better communication over the tradition &4bug&n/&4typo&n/&4idea&n commands which logs
the text directly to file which usually ends up being ignored.

&3Lifecycle&n
&3---------&n
Initially when a report is created, the state is set to &3OPEN&n. When the
responsible person looks at the report, they should edit it and change the
state to &3ASSESSED&n (so the reporter knows the report has been looked at).
The responsible person should then fix/respond to the problem and change
the state to &3FEEDBACK&n. The reporter then verifies the fix/responce and
edits the report changing the state to &3CLOSED&n. Obvious exceptions apply to
a more complicated report, but the state principals as mentioned above
should be used consistantly as described.

Reports which have the &3DELETED&n state are still kept in file, but are not
visible from within the game.

&3Notification&n
&3------------&n
Every time that a report is modified, notification is given to the involved
parties (all people that have made a change to the initial report). This
notification is in the form of mudmail and includes the change description
as well information on how to view the entire details.

&3Restrictions&n
&3------------&n
Various restrictions have been put into the reporting system to ensure that
the system runs smoothly and as intended (holds appropiate privacy).

There are some restrictions that apply when using the report editor, but the
main restriction that apply on report usage are as follows:

Command      	list/print                      edit/delete
-------		----------			-----------
&3BUG&n          	<  GOD - owned reports          <  GRGOD - owned reports
		>= GOD - all reports            >= GRGOD - all reports

&3IDEA&n         	<  ANGEL - owned reports        <  GRGOD - owned reports
		>= ANGEL - all reports          >= GRGOD - all reports

&3TYPO&n         	<  IMMORT - owned reports       <  GOD - owned reports
              	>= IMMORT - all reports         >= GOD - all reports

&3TODO&n         	<  ANGEL - owned reports        <  GRGOD - owned reports
		>= ANGEL - all reports          >= GRGOD - all reports


See also: &3BUG IDEA TODO TYPO LISTREPORTS PRINTREPORT&n
#
BUY

&2Buy&n

&3Usage:&n &4buy <item name>
       buy #<item number>
       buy n.<item name>
       buy n <item name>
       buy n #<item number>&n

If you'd like to purchase an item from a shop and have the money, you can buy
it.  Items can be bought by name, or by their number in the shop listing,
and can be bought in quantity.
 
Examples:
 
  > buy sword        (buy the first sword on the list)
  > buy #3           (buy the third item on the list)
  > buy 4.sword      (buy the fourth sword on the list)
  > buy 10 bread     (buy 10 pieces of bread)
  > buy 10 #2        (buy 10 of the second item on the list)
 
See also: &3LIST, SELL, SHOPS, VALUE&n
#
